006.","meanings":["Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of   Katz  .","Americanized form of German   Katz  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Katz","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hyman, Isadore, Meyer, Moshe, Chaim, Emanuel, Aron, Mayer, Shoshana, Zev.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): acronymic surname from the first letters of the Hebrew phrase <i>kohen tsedek</i> ‘priest of righteousness’ (see   Cohen  ).","German: nickname from <i>Katz(e)</i> ‘cat’. See also English   Catt  , compare   Catz   and   Kates  ."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":37,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Roger de Cauz was born in 1178, in Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Nicole Leigh in 1207, in Shirland, Derbyshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1219, in Shirland, Derbyshire, England, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1178–1219":"1178–1219","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1215":"1215","1178":"1178","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","Shirland, Derbyshire, England":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1178–1219":"1178–1219","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1215":"1215","1178":"1178","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","Shirland, Derbyshire, England":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"1178–1219":"1178–1219","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1215":"1215","1178":"1178","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, Angleterre","Shirland, Derbyshire, England":"Shirland, Derbyshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Roger de Cauz est né en 1178, à Shalbourne, Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Nicole Leigh en 1207, à Shirland, Derbyshire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1219, à Shirland, Derbyshire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 41 ans."},"de":{"1178–1219":"1178–1219","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1215":"1215","1178":"1178","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","Shirland, Derbyshire, England":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England","lifeSummary":"Roger de Cauz wurde 1178 in Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom gebore